 helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">10.3 km. Park where a barely discernable old alder-infested road leads off to the east. This route approaches the mountain from the northwest. Head for a shoulder of Ladybird that leads up to the west ridge.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Route:\u00a0 <\/strong>Follow this road for 2 hours and a kilometre of bushwhacking through alder. The general direction is east then south along an unnamed creek coming from the SW side of Ladybird. 3 washouts obliterate the road. \u00a0The road ends in a mature forest and ascend the shoulder. Where the ridge is joined is too far west and several ups and downs are on the traverse. Leave the ridge heading for a talus slope and ascend the SW shoulder to the summit.<br \/>\n<em><strong>Descend<\/strong><\/em> from the col along the ridge and shorten the trip.<strong> \u00a0<\/strong>\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Good views are towards Nelson, the Valhallas and Mt Faith, Pallisades, Airy and Kamikaze.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Routes that use Rialto Road (just past Keenleyside Dam) approach Ladybird from the southeast and should be investigated to see if the bushwhack could be lessened.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>LADYBIRD MT \u00a0\u00a02263m \u00a07425&#8242; The described route was enjoyable mountaineering but the bushwhack to get there was awful.\u00a0 Difficulty: C3 a terrible bushwhack\u00a0 Elevation gain: Key elevations: Distance: Time: 8 hours. Map: Drive: From Castlegar, drive 10 km up Pass &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/10\/12\/ladybird-mountain\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping